                    <msContents>
                        <summary> Explanation of difficult words in al-Maḳāmāt al-Hindīyah (The
                            Indian Assemblies) (see JRL Arabic MS 313 [Mingana catalogue no. 702],
                            no yet digitised).</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="manuscript_14142-item1">
                            <title key="" xml:lang="en" type="desc">Explanation of difficult words
                                in al-Maqāmāt al-Hindīyah</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                            <note><p>No author's name is found in the short preamble, but at the end
                                    on folio 10b the name Muḥammad al-Hāshim
                                        al-Darquṭni<persName>مهمد الهاشم الدرقطني</persName> occurs.
                                    According to Mingana, this person was probably the author of the
                                    work and he must have lived around 1790 CE. From the wording of
                                    the colophon it appears that the manuscript is an autograph of
                                    Darquṭni.</p>
                                <p>The number of maqamahs is written on the margins, and at the end
                                    occurs the following inscription (in the same hand): <quote
                                        xml:lang="ar">تم الاصلاح في المقامات الهندية
                                </quote>.</p></note>
                            <incipit>الحمد لله الرحمن الرحيم... لا فوقه العليم ططط وبعد فهذا تضيل
                                لما اجمل تسهيل لما اشكل في المقامات الجندية من المقامات
                                الهندية</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
