                                ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208">India</placeName>
                            <date calendar="#Gregorian" from="1823" to="1867"> from 1823 to
                                1867</date>, latterly as Commissioner of <placeName
                                    ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7001535">Delhi</placeName>. He
                            acquired over a thousand Indian and Persian manuscripts, from which the
                            <orgName type="standard" key="person_134857252">British
                                Museum</orgName> selected 352, now held in the <orgName
                                    type="standard" key="person_121814978">British Library</orgName>;
                            his ownership inscription on <locus from="flyleaf_ia">flyleaf
                                ia</locus>: <quote xml:lang="ar">كرنيل جارج وليم هملتن صاحب
